{"title_page": "Cool warehouse", "text_new": "A '''cool warehouse''' or '''cold storage warehouse''' is a [[warehouse]] where [[perishable|perishable goods]] are stored and [[Refrigeration|refrigerated]]. Products stored can be, amongst other things, [[food]], especially [[meat]], other [[agriculture|agricultural products]], [[pharmaceutical drug]]s, other [[chemical substance|chemicals]] and [[blood]].<ref>{{Cite journal|date=1916|title=New Jersey: Foodstuffs. Cold Storage. Regulation of. (Ch. 101, Act Mar. 16, 1916)|journal= \tPublic Health Reports|volume=31|issue=31|pages=2122\u20132124|jstor=4573937}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Holmes|first=George K.|date=1913|title=Prevention of Waste and Seasonal Price Fluctuations Through Refrigeration|journal=The Annals of the American Academy of Political and Social Science|volume=50|pages=48\u201356|doi=10.1177/000271621305000107|jstor=1012671|url=https://zenodo.org/record/2396535}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Warehouses]]\n[[Category:Cooling technology]]\n[[Category:Food preservation]]\n\n\n{{technology-stub}}\n", "text_old": "A '''cool warehouse''' or '''cold storage warehouse''' is a [[warehouse]] were [[perishable|perishable goods]] are stored and [[Refrigeration|refrigerated]]. Products stored can be, amongst other things, [[food]], especially [[meat]], other [[agriculture|agricultural products]], [[pharmaceutical drug]]s, other [[chemical substance|chemicals]] and [[blood]].<ref>{{Cite journal|date=1916|title=New Jersey: Foodstuffs. Cold Storage. Regulation of. (Ch. 101, Act Mar. 16, 1916)|journal= \tPublic Health Reports|volume=31|issue=31|pages=2122\u20132124|jstor=4573937}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Holmes|first=George K.|date=1913|title=Prevention of Waste and Seasonal Price Fluctuations Through Refrigeration|journal=The Annals of the American Academy of Political and Social Science|volume=50|pages=48\u201356|doi=10.1177/000271621305000107|jstor=1012671|url=https://zenodo.org/record/2396535}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Warehouses]]\n[[Category:Cooling technology]]\n[[Category:Food preservation]]\n\n\n{{technology-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Johnsoniensis", "label": "safe", "comment": "spllg", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cool_warehouse"}
{"title_page": "Thierry Plas", "text_new": "'''Thierry Patrick Plas''' (born 1959) is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] [[guitarist]], first known as lead guitarist and co-songwriter for the Belgian [[rock music|rock]] [[Musical ensemble|group]] [[Machiavel (band)|Machiavel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://machiavel.be/about/|title=The history of that belgian band called Machiavel|work=Machiavel|accessdate=16 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.belgian-beatles-society.com/about-us/the-advisory-board|title=The Advisory Board|author=Administrator|work=belgian-beatles-society.com|accessdate=16 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | last=Strong | first=M.C. | title=The Great Indie Discography | publisher=Canongate | year=2003 | isbn=978-1-84195-335-9 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HJfGtREyuSAC&pg=PA249 | language=de | ref=harv | accessdate=2015-11-16}}</ref> Since 1992, Plas composes and produces also soundtracks for the film and advertising industry at ZOO Productions Company.\n\n== Biography ==\nAt the age of 21, he joined Machiavel at a time when the band was going through fundamental (personnel) changes, and looking for a new direction. This led to more of a [[hard rock]] sound, combined with greater maturity and simplicity, culminating in the hit single \"Fly\" from their 1980 album \"New Lines\". \nIn the 1990s, Thierry Plas became a highly appreciated session musician, playing live and recording with [[Vaya Con Dios (band)|Vaya Con Dios]], [[Vladimir Cosma]], Pierre Rapsat, [[Beverly Jo Scott]], [[Billy Preston]] and other Belgian, French & international artists.\n\nPlas was also a member of '''The Responsibles''' with Patrick Riguelle who released one album, \"Every Germ is Sacred\" (1995) and were chosen as the opening act for [[Jimmy Page]] & [[Robert Plant]] in [[Brussels]], [[Rotterdam]] and [[K\u00f6ln]].\n\nIn 2000, Plas and Marc Ysaye (of Machiavel) teamed up again to record the Purple Prose album with [[Dani Klein]], and in 2004 Thierry did arrangements & guitars for several tracks on the\nalbum of [[Vaya Con Dios (band)|Vaya Con Dios]] \"The Promise\".  Under the pseudonym \"Michel Vaillant\", he also participated in several hip-hop successes. Other production credits over the years have included Belgium's 1988 Eurovision candidate [[Reynaert|Joseph Reynaerts]], Brandthout, [[Klaus Klang]] and [[Raxola]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/artist/483581-Thierry-Plas?page=3|title=Thierry Plas|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2018-01-18}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.machiavel.be/ Machiavel, official site]\n* [http://www.tailorsofpanama.com/ The Tailors of Panama, official site]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Plas, Thierry}}\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Belgian rock guitarists]]\n[[Category:Belgian film score composers]]\n[[Category:Male film score composers]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "'''Thierry Patrick Plas''' (born 1959) is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] [[guitarist]], first known as lead guitarist and co-songwriter for the Belgian [[rock music|rock]] [[Musical ensemble|group]] [[Machiavel (band)|Machiavel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://machiavel.be/about/|title=The history of that belgian band called Machiavel|work=Machiavel|accessdate=16 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.belgian-beatles-society.com/about-us/the-advisory-board|title=The Advisory Board|author=Administrator|work=belgian-beatles-society.com|accessdate=16 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | last=Strong | first=M.C. | title=The Great Indie Discography | publisher=Canongate | year=2003 | isbn=978-1-84195-335-9 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HJfGtREyuSAC&pg=PA249 | language=de | ref=harv | accessdate=2015-11-16}}</ref> Since 1992, Plas composes and produces also soundtracks for the film and advertising industry at ZOO Productions Company.\n\n== Biography ==\nAt the age of 21, he joined Machiavel at a time when the band was going through fundamental (personnel) changes, and looking for a new direction. This led to more of a [[hard rock]] sound, combined with greater maturity and simplicity, culminating in the hit single \"Fly\" from their 1980 album \"New Lines\". \nIn the 1990s, Thierry Plas became a highly appreciated session musician, playing live and recording with [[Vaya Con Dios (band)|Vaya Con Dios]], [[Vladimir Cosma]], Pierre Rapsat, [[Beverly Jo Scott]], [[Billy Preston]] and other Belgian, French & international artists.\n\nThierry Plas was also a member of '''The Responsibles''' with Patrick Riguelle who released one album, \"Every Germ is Sacred\" (1995) and were chosen as the opening act for [[Jimmy Page]] & [[Robert Plant]] in [[Brussels]], [[Rotterdam]] and [[K\u00f6ln]].\n\nIn 2000, Plas and Marc Ysaye (of Machiavel) teamed up again to record the Purple Prose album with [[Dani Klein]], and in 2004 Thierry did arrangements & guitars for several tracks on the\nalbum of [[Vaya Con Dios (band)|Vaya Con Dios]] \"The Promise\".  Under the pseudonym \"Michel Vaillant\", he also participated in several hip-hop successes. Other production credits over the years have included Belgium's 1988 Eurovision candidate [[Reynaert|Joseph Reynaerts]], Brandthout, [[Klaus Klang]] and [[Raxola]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/artist/483581-Thierry-Plas?page=3|title=Thierry Plas|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2018-01-18}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.machiavel.be/ Machiavel, official site]\n* [http://www.tailorsofpanama.com/ The Tailors of Panama, official site]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Plas, Thierry}}\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Belgian rock guitarists]]\n[[Category:Belgian film score composers]]\n[[Category:Male film score composers]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "name_user": "Refcheck", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBiography", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thierry_Plas"}
